## Overview
* * *
### The Cyberpunk Scfi Setting


### It's a city of dreams
*   Cyberpunk 2077 was a bold and ambitious title that was aiming to tackle and package what were crowning gameplay elements of other multiple Open World genres. The expectations set upon this game and the promised experience was set to encompass:
    *   Immersive sim elements on par to a game like Deus Ex.
    *   An open world that is brimming with activity and life that could rival GTA
    *   A narratively branching experience, with deep RPG skillsets and character builds similar to Fallout New Vegas.
*   CDProjectRed weren't shy to say that they were aiming to create the ultimate Open World experience for players.

*   In a lot of ways Cyberpunk was a Litmus Test for a lot of the YouTube Reviewer channels.

### Cyberpunk is not a Soulless Game

*   I have seen many compare Cyberpunk to the likes of Fallout 76 and Anthem. I feel that this is an unfair comparison here. Whilst at release on a technical level particularly on consoles this game was a technical disaster with Sony having to remove the game from being purchased. I still believe that if Anthem or Fallout 76 released with no bugs and were stable releases, these games at launch would still be inherently flawed. However if Cyberpunk released free of the myriad of technical issues it faced at launch, it would have been a much more well received game.
*   It is up for debate on whether it delivered and achieved the heights of ambition promised, but overall I would say most would have enjoyed the game, but felt there could have been more.
*   The best comparison I make here is similar to the release of Fallout 4. If Cyberpunk had released in a bugless state the discourse around the game still would have been divisive, however the conversation would be centred around it's quality as an RPG,  and I'm willing to bet most would have said they enjoyed playing the game.

### An Incredible Open World, missing it's masterstroke
#### Night City feels Incredible
- Night City is huge in scope and size, spanning across many regions.  However Night City's open world is filled with tons of verticality from a variety of high rise complexes you can walk through and explore. 
- The contrast and distinction between each region of Night City is clear and vivid in it's own unique way lending to an environment that tells the player a story of the world around them and their inhabitancies.
